SIMPLE: scrofulous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrofulous
<hw>Scrof"u*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>scrofuleux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to scrofula,
or partaking of its nature; <as>as, <ex>scrofulous</ex> tumors; a
<ex>scrofulous</ex> habit of body</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Diseased or affected with scrofula.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Scrofulous</qex> persons can never be duly nourished.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Scrof"u*lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Scrof"u*lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrog</ent>⟦br⟧
